  "texts": [
    "We first demonstrate the applicability of our predictors by examining the generalizability of sequence-ensemble relationships in IDRs.",
    "Then, we leverage the high-throughput nature of ALBATROSS to characterize the sequence-specific biophysical behavior of IDRs within and between proteomes.",
    "IDRs make up an estimated 30% of most eukaryotic proteomes and play a variety of roles in molecular and cellular function [1] [2] [3] [4].",
    "Although folded domains are often well described by a single (or small number of) three-dimensional (3D) structures, IDRs are defined by extensive conformational heterogeneity.",
    "This means that they exist in a conformational ensemble (a collection of rapidly interconverting states that prohibits structural classification by any single reference structure)."
  ],
